# TodayPlus Personalization System - Complete Implementation Guide for Cursor

## Overview

This document contains EVERYTHING needed to implement the TodayPlus personalization system. It includes the full article pipeline, database schema, API endpoints, complete AI prompts (not shortened), and frontend components.

---

# PART 1: SYSTEM ARCHITECTURE

## How The System Works

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                           ARTICLE PIPELINE                                   │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│                                                                              │
│  1. RSS FEEDS (news sources)                                                │
│         ↓                                                                    │
│  2. APPROVAL PROMPT (AI decides: APPROVED or ELIMINATED)                    │
│         ↓                                                                    │
│  3. SCORING PROMPT (AI assigns base_score 700-950)                          │
│         ↓                                                                    │
│  4. TAGGING PROMPT (AI assigns countries + topics)                          │
│         ↓                                                                    │
│  5. DATABASE (store article with score + tags)                              │
│         ↓                                                                    │
│  6. PERSONALIZATION ENGINE (calculate final_score per user)                 │
│         ↓                                                                    │
│  7. USER FEEDS ("Today" feed + "For You" feed)                              │
│                                                                              │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

## Two Feeds Explained

| Feed | Description | Sorting | Content |
|------|-------------|---------|---------|
| **"Today"** | Global top stories that everyone should know | `base_score` only (no personalization) | Top 10-15 articles with base_score ≥ 880, same for all users |
| **"For You"** | Personalized feed based on user's interests | `final_score` (base_score + boosts) | Unlimited articles, different for each user based on their preferences |

**Why Two Feeds?**
- "Today" ensures users don't miss globally important news (wars, major events, etc.)
- "For You" makes users feel the app understands their interests
- Users can switch between them based on what they want

