# PART 2: DATABASE SCHEMA

## Table 1: `articles`

Stores all approved articles with their scores and tags.

```sql
CREATE TABLE articles (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT uuid_generate_v4(),
  title TEXT NOT NULL,
  url TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,
  source TEXT NOT NULL,
  category TEXT NOT NULL,
  base_score INTEGER NOT NULL CHECK (base_score >= 700 AND base_score <= 950),
  countries TEXT[] DEFAULT '{}',
  topics TEXT[] DEFAULT '{}',
  image_url TEXT,
  description TEXT,
  published_at TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE,
  created_at TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE DEFAULT NOW(),
  updated_at TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE DEFAULT NOW()
);

-- Indexes for fast queries
CREATE INDEX idx_articles_base_score ON articles(base_score DESC);
CREATE INDEX idx_articles_countries ON articles USING GIN(countries);
CREATE INDEX idx_articles_topics ON articles USING GIN(topics);
CREATE INDEX idx_articles_created_at ON articles(created_at DESC);
CREATE INDEX idx_articles_category ON articles(category);
```

**Column Explanations:**
- `base_score`: Global importance score (700-950) assigned by AI
- `countries`: Array of country codes this article is about (e.g., `["usa", "china"]`)
- `topics`: Array of topic codes this article covers (e.g., `["economics", "geopolitics"]`)
- `category`: Display category (World, Politics, Business, Tech, Sports, etc.)

## Table 2: `users`

Stores user preferences for personalization.

```sql
CREATE TABLE users (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT uuid_generate_v4(),
  email TEXT UNIQUE,
  home_country TEXT NOT NULL,
  followed_countries TEXT[] DEFAULT '{}',
  followed_topics TEXT[] NOT NULL,
  onboarding_completed BOOLEAN DEFAULT FALSE,
  created_at TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE DEFAULT NOW(),
  updated_at TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE DEFAULT NOW(),
  
  -- Validation constraints
  CONSTRAINT valid_home_country CHECK (home_country = ANY(ARRAY[
    'usa', 'uk', 'china', 'russia', 'germany', 'france', 'italy', 'spain', 
    'ukraine', 'turkiye', 'japan', 'south_korea', 'india', 'taiwan', 
    'israel', 'saudi_arabia', 'iran', 'uae', 'canada', 'brazil', 'mexico', 'australia'
  ])),
  CONSTRAINT min_topics CHECK (array_length(followed_topics, 1) >= 3),
  CONSTRAINT max_topics CHECK (array_length(followed_topics, 1) <= 10),
  CONSTRAINT max_followed_countries CHECK (array_length(followed_countries, 1) <= 5)
);

CREATE INDEX idx_users_home_country ON users(home_country);
```

**Column Explanations:**
- `home_country`: User's primary country (gets highest boost, +150)
- `followed_countries`: Additional countries user wants to follow (max 5, gets +75/+100 boost)
- `followed_topics`: Topics user is interested in (min 3, max 10, gets +50/+80/+100 boost)
- `onboarding_completed`: Whether user has completed the initial setup

## Table 3: `reading_history` (For Future Use)

Track what users read for implicit personalization later.

```sql
CREATE TABLE reading_history (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT uuid_generate_v4(),
  user_id UUID REFERENCES users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  article_id UUID REFERENCES articles(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  read_at TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE DEFAULT NOW(),
  time_spent_seconds INTEGER,
  
  UNIQUE(user_id, article_id)
);

CREATE INDEX idx_reading_history_user ON reading_history(user_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_reading_history_article ON reading_history(article_id);
```

